==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flume
<hw>Flume</hw> <pr>(f;⟦umac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OE.
<ets>flum</ets> river, OF, <ets>flum</ets>, fr. L. <ets>flumen</ets>,
fr. <ets>fluere</ets> to flow. ⟦root⟧84. See <er>Fluent</er>.]</ety>
<def>A stream; especially, a passage channel, or conduit for the water
that drives a mill wheel; or an artificial channel of water for
hydraulic or placer mining; also, a chute for conveying logs or lumber
down a declivity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fluminous</ent>⟦br⟧
